cording to the expected outcomes theoretically projected by the program code and working principles <mark class="nova-legacy-e-text-highlight nova-legacy-e-text-highlight--color-yellow">[10]</mark>. The system Schematic is shown in Fig. 4. When the Rail crosses through either IR(R) or IR(L); then the sensor outputs a HIGH voltage across the resistor R3 and R2 respectively, which are fed to the ADC(1) and ADC (2) of ATmega16 accordingly; to close the crossing gate by moving the stepper motor driven in clock wise direction through the motor driver ULN2003A.  ...</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="nova-legacy-c-tooltip__arrow nova-legacy-c-tooltip__arrow nova-legacy-c-tooltip__arrow--body"><div class="nova-legacy-c-tooltip__arrow-tip"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="nova-legacy-o-stack__item"><div class="nova-legacy-v-citation-item__context-source"><div itemProp="citation" itemscope="" itemType="http://schema.org/ScholarlyArticle" class="nova-legacy-v-publication-item nova-legacy-v-publication-item--size-m gtm-figure-citation-item"><div class="nova-legacy-v-publication-item__body"><div class="nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack--gutter-m"><div class="nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack-item"><div class="nova-legacy-e-text nova-legacy-e-text--size-l nova-legacy-e-text--family-sans-serif nova-legacy-e-text--spacing-none nova-legacy-e-text--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-text--clamp-2 nova-legacy-v-publication-item__title" itemProp="headline"><a class="nova-legacy-e-link nova-legacy-e-link--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-link--theme-bare" href="publication/345085994_Into_the_Binary_World_of_Zero_Death_Toll_by_Implementing_a_Sustainable_Powered_Automatic_Railway_Gate_Control_System">Into the Binary World of Zero Death Toll by Implementing a Sustainable Powered Automatic Railway Gate Control System</a></div></div><div class="nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack-item"><div class="nova-legacy-v-publication